TITLE: Florida Covid-19 hospitalizations up 13% from previous peak in July 2020
SUMMARY: Coronavirus-related hospitalizations are up 13% from Florida's previous peak on July 23, 2020, according to the Florida Hospital Association.

TITLE: Missouri governor pardons St. Louis couple who pointed guns at protesters
SUMMARY: Missouri Republican Gov. Mike Parson on Tuesday announced pardons for Patricia and Mark McCloskey, the St. Louis homeowners who pointed guns at protesters near their home last summer.

TITLE: Opinion: The speed of the US economic recovery has been record-breaking. But don't get used to it
SUMMARY: Despite the continued optimism about the country reopening, US economic growth is already starting to slow.

TITLE: More than $170,000 raised in 24 hours for mother and three kids facing eviction
SUMMARY: On Monday, Dasha Kelly was facing eviction and didn't know how she was going to pay her back rent. A day later, thanks to strangers, more than $170,000 has been raised so far for her and her three daughters.

TITLE: Joe Biden is having the worst week of his presidency so far
SUMMARY: Joe Biden's presidential honeymoon has officially ended, with a series of problems -- led by the ongoing surge of the Delta variant of the coronavirus -- coalescing to make the last few days some of the worst ones he has spent as president.

TITLE: A Trump endorsement and the backing of the Democratic establishment were key to Ohio primary election results
SUMMARY: In two Ohio congressional primaries Tuesday, Democratic voters embraced the party's establishment, delivering President Joe Biden another ally and denying the left-wing "Squad" its latest member. Republicans, meanwhile, stuck with former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Mike Carey, endorsed by Trump, will win Ohio GOP special primary
SUMMARY: Mike Carey, a coal lobbyist who was endorsed by former President Donald Trump, will win the Republican special primary in Ohio's 15th Congressional District, CNN projects.

TITLE: Shontel Brown will win Ohio Democratic special primary
SUMMARY: Cuyahoga County Council member Shontel Brown is set to win the Democratic special primary in Ohio's 11th Congressional District after her opponent Nina Turner conceded Tuesday night.

TITLE: NBC's Summer Olympics ratings are in free-fall
SUMMARY: After pandemic-fueled delays last year, the Tokyo Olympics have gotten a lot of attention around this summer. Unfortunately for NBC, that attention has not translated to viewership.

TITLE: Meet the new meme stock: Robinhood soars 82%
SUMMARY: Robinhood cashed in on the meme stock craze. Now Robinhood itself is turning into the next plaything for the retail trading crowd.

TITLE: CVS will raise its minimum wage to $15 an hour
SUMMARY: CVS will raise its minimum wage for hourly workers from $11 to $15 by next summer, becoming the latest large US chain to pledge a $15 starting rate as companies compete for workers in a tight labor market.

TITLE: China's biggest private companies are in chaos. It's all part of Beijing's plan
SUMMARY: China's crackdown on private enterprise has wiped out more than $1.2 trillion in market value for many powerful Chinese companies and stoked fears about the future of innovation in the world's second largest economy.
